docs.abstract: Pressed to explain its connections to Beijing, the American arm of China’s state broadcaster claimed independence. Now, key employees have been recalled to China.
docs.snippet: Pressed to explain its connections to Beijing, the American arm of China’s state broadcaster claimed independence. Now, key employees have been recalled to China.
docs.lead_paragraph: China’s state broadcaster is recalling the head of its American arm and more than a dozen other employees back to China in a leadership shake-up as scrutiny grows in the United States over the unit’s connections to Beijing.

headline.main: Facing Legal Scrutiny, China’s State TV Recalls Its U.S. Head

docs.abstract: The Hollywood Reporter portrayed a situation in which the chairman of Warner Bros., Kevin Tsujihara, pushed for a woman with whom he had a sexual relationship to be considered for film and TV roles.
docs.snippet: The Hollywood Reporter portrayed a situation in which the chairman of Warner Bros., Kevin Tsujihara, pushed for a woman with whom he had a sexual relationship to be considered for film and TV roles.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — WarnerMedia said on Wednesday that it would conduct an “appropriate investigation” into allegations that Kevin Tsujihara, the chief executive of Warner Bros., pushed for a woman with whom he had a sexual relationship to be considered for roles in Warner films and television shows.

headline.main: WarnerMedia to Investigate Claims Involving a Top Executive
headline.print_headline: Warner Media Will Investigate Whether Executive Helped Actress in Relationship Get Roles

docs.abstract: Policymakers unexpectedly reinstated a program meant to encourage banks to lend, a sign that its concerns extend beyond the immediate region.
docs.snippet: Policymakers unexpectedly reinstated a program meant to encourage banks to lend, a sign that its concerns extend beyond the immediate region.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — Just a few months ago, the European Central Bank put the brakes on a vast economic stimulus program devised during the financial crisis. On Thursday, it unexpectedly reversed course and revived some of the measures, signaling the rising threat of a recession.

headline.main: Global Economy Slows, Pushing Europe’s Central Bank to Make a Surprise Move

docs.abstract: The group, including schools like M.I.T. and Stanford, aims to train the next generation of leaders to develop and regulate technology for the public good.

docs.abstract: The payment to Amit Singhal, who ran Google’s search division and was accused of groping an employee, was revealed on Monday in a shareholder lawsuit.
docs.snippet: The payment to Amit Singhal, who ran Google’s search division and was accused of groping an employee, was revealed on Monday in a shareholder lawsuit.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Alphabet’s board of directors agreed to pay a former top Google executive as much as $45 million when he resigned from the company in 2016 after being accused of groping a subordinate.

headline.main: Google Approved $45 Million Exit Package for Executive Accused of Misconduct
headline.print_headline: Google Executive Accused of Groping Got $45 Million

docs.abstract: American negotiators insist that agriculture be included in a prospective trade deal while European officials say the topic was never up for discussion, jeopardizing talks before they even begin.
docs.snippet: American negotiators insist that agriculture be included in a prospective trade deal while European officials say the topic was never up for discussion, jeopardizing talks before they even begin.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After a White House meeting last July, President Trump and Jean-Claude Juncker, the European Commission president, stepped into the Rose Garden and proclaimed they had a trade deal or, at the very least, the makings of a future pact.

headline.main: U.S. and E.U. Are Headed for a Food Fight Over Trade
headline.print_headline: U.S. and E.U.  Go to Corners In Food Fight

docs.abstract: CGTN America, which is based in Washington and available in 30 million United States households, insists it does not do Beijing’s bidding. Some people are skeptical.
docs.snippet: CGTN America, which is based in Washington and available in 30 million United States households, insists it does not do Beijing’s bidding. Some people are skeptical.
docs.lead_paragraph: It broadcasts forced confessions to American audiences. It avoids subjects that displease Beijing. It cuts away when wind musses the hair of Xi Jinping, the Chinese president.

headline.main: Live From America’s Capital, a TV Station Run by China’s Communist Party
headline.print_headline: China Airs Propaganda In the U.S. on Live TV
